<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-647] Two small bugs in seq2sparse</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-647</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Vasil on the mailing list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. the minLLR parameter is not taken into account. The problem is that in&lt;br/&gt;
the CollocDriver class&lt;br/&gt;
Job job = new Job(conf);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is executed before&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;conf.setFloat(LLRReducer.MIN_LLR, minLLRValue);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;see CollocDriver.computeNGramsPruneByLLR method&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. maxDFPercent is not taken into account. The problem is that in&lt;br/&gt;
TFIDFPartialVectorReducer.reduce the check is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (df / vectorCount &amp;gt; maxDfPercent) {&lt;br/&gt;
         if (log.isInfoEnabled()) {&lt;br/&gt;
               log.info(&quot;ommiting {}&quot;, e.index());&lt;br/&gt;
             }&lt;br/&gt;
       continue;&lt;br/&gt;
     }&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (df*100 / vectorCount &amp;gt; maxDfPercent) {&lt;br/&gt;
         if (log.isInfoEnabled()) {&lt;br/&gt;
               log.info(&quot;ommiting {}&quot;, e.index());&lt;br/&gt;
             }&lt;br/&gt;
       continue;&lt;br/&gt;
     }&lt;/p&gt;</description>
